pcubeConfigCopyMIB.name: pcubeConfigCopyMIB

revisions.description: The original mib has been chagned to use SMIv2 syntax. Clarified descriptions in the mib.
Initial version of this MIB module.

pcubeConfigCopyMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-sce@cisco.com
pcubeConfigCopyMIB.description: This MIB facilitates writing of running configuration of the SCOS to startup configuration. A config-copy operation is a request to copy a configuration file of a running SCOS. The term 'agent-config' will be used in this MIB to refer to either the running config or the startup config. The term SCE refers to Service Control Engine

ConfigFileType.name: ConfigFileType
ConfigFileType.description: The various types of files on which a config-copy operation can be performed.

pcubeCopyEntry.name: pcubeCopyEntry
pcubeCopyEntry.description: A config-copy request. A management station wishing to save the running config may use any number to be used as an index. The station should then create the associated instance of the row status and row index objects. It should be noted however that currently 'pcubeCopySourceFileType' must be of 'runningConfig' type and 'pcubeCopyDestFileType' must be of 'startupConfig' type (that are the default values). After setting pcubeCopySourceFileType and pcubeCopyDestFileType objects by explicit SNMP request or or by default, the row status should be set to createAndGo to initiate the request. Note that this entire procedure may be initiated via a single set request which specifies a row status of 'createAndGo(4)'.

pcubeCopyIndex.name: pcubeCopyIndex
pcubeCopyIndex.description: Object which specifies a unique entry in the pcubeCopyTable. A management station wishing to initiate a config-copy operation should use a random value for this object when creating or modifying an instance of a 'pcubeCopyEntry'. The RowStatus semantics of the 'pcubeCopyEntryRowStatus' object will prevent access conflicts.

pcubeCopyEntryRowStatus.name: pcubeCopyEntryRowStatus
pcubeCopyEntryRowStatus.description: This object can be used for creating/deleting entries from the table.

pcubeCopySourceFileType.name: pcubeCopySourceFileType
pcubeCopySourceFileType.description: Specifies the type of file to copy from. Currently only 'runningConfig(2)' is supported.

pcubeCopyDestFileType.name: pcubeCopyDestFileType
pcubeCopyDestFileType.description: Specifies the type of file to copy to. currently only 'startupConfig(1)' is supported.

pcubeConfigCopyMIBCompliance.name: pcubeConfigCopyMIBCompliance
pcubeConfigCopyMIBCompliance.description: A compliance statement defined in this MIB module, for SCE SNMP agents.

pcubeCopyGroup.name: pcubeCopyGroup
pcubeCopyGroup.description: A collection of objects used for specifying the configuration of the copy operation.
